(-1, 'Welcome to TNSTC Electronics and Communication', '<span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\">This Website is to help you understand the basics of Electronics and Communication.</span><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\"><br></span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\">We have Lots of content which you can browse from and learn</span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\"><br></span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\">Use the Navigation Bar to go through the various subtopics&nbsp;</span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\"><br></span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\">We have also Included a quiz to Help you test your Understanding of Electronics</span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\"><br></span></div><div style=\\\"\\\"><span style=\\\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\\\" arial=\\\"\\\" black\\\";=\\\"\\\" color:=\\\"\\\" rgb(0,=\\\"\\\" 0,=\\\"\\\" 153);\\\"=\\\"\\\">Have Fun and Keep on Learning!</span></div>', 'communication', 'Electronics', 0, '-1', 'A', 'index'),
(17, 'Semiconductors', '<h3 style=\\\"\\\">What is it that drives our phones and computers?</h3><h3 style=\\\"\\\">What is it that runs the machines we use?</h3><h3 style=\\\"\\\">To learn more about these wonder metals, Click on the Subtopics bar to begin</h3><div style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\"><img src=\\\"manage-site/images/S2.jpg\\\"></div>', 'electronics', 'Various electronics', 0, '-1', 'A', 'semiconductors'),
(19, 'Introduction to Semiconductors', '<p></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">A semiconductor is a substance, usually a\r\nsolid chemical element or compound that can conduct electricity under some\r\nconditions but not others, making it a good medium for the control of\r\nelectrical current. In a semiconductor material, the flow of holes occurs in a direction\r\nopposite to the flow of electrons.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">Example:&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nSilicon, Germanium, Selenium.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">It has a conductivity between that of\r\nmetal and an insulator.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">The conductivity of Conductivity&nbsp; &gt;&nbsp;\r\nConductivity of semiconductor&nbsp;\r\n&gt; Conductivity of insulator.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">The resistance of Conductivity&nbsp; &lt;&nbsp;\r\nResistance of semiconductor&nbsp; &lt;\r\nResistance of insulator.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">We know that&nbsp; Resistance is a property that indicates the\r\nopposition to the flow of current.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"text-align:center;line-height:normal\\\"><b><span style=\\\"color:#222222;background:white;\r\nmso-highlight:white\\\">R= ρl/A<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">Here ρ is resistivity which also\r\nindicates as same resistance.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" align=\\\"center\\\" style=\\\"text-align:center;line-height:normal\\\"><b><span style=\\\"background:white;mso-highlight:\r\nwhite\\\">σ=1/ρ</span></b><span style=\\\"background:white;mso-highlight:white\\\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#222222;\r\nbackground:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">Here </span><b><span style=\\\"color:#5F6368;background:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">σ </span></b><span style=\\\"color:#5F6368;background:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">i</span><span style=\\\"background:white;mso-highlight:white\\\">s conductivity which is inversely\r\nproportional to resistivity, so it indicates the flow of current.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height:normal\\\"><span style=\\\"background:white;\r\nmso-highlight:white\\\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><table class=\\\"MsoNormalTable\\\" border=\\\"1\\\" cellspacing=\\\"0\\\" cellpadding=\\\"0\\\" width=\\\"0\\\" style=\\\"border-collapse:collapse;mso-table-layout-alt:fixed;border:none;\r\n mso-border-alt:solid #A2A9B1 .75pt;mso-yfti-tbllook:1536;mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n mso-border-insideh:.75pt solid #A2A9B1;mso-border-insidev:.75pt solid #A2A9B1\\\">\r\n <tbody><tr style=\\\"mso-yfti-irow:0;mso-yfti-firstrow:yes;height:16.5pt\\\">\r\n  <td width=\\\"121\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\" style=\\\"width:88.5pt;border:solid #A2A9B1 1.0pt;\r\n  mso-border-alt:s